@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<div class="card">
    <div class="card-body">
<h1 class="card-title">BookStore - Blazor and API Application</h1>
        <p class="card-text">
            .NET 10 Book Store Web API consume by Blazor Server and WASM Apps.
            By doing this course, you would have:
            <ul>
                <li>Build a fully data driven REST Web API .NET 10 using cutting edge technology</li>
                <li>Connect to a Database using Entity Framework Core</li>
                <li>Responsing Pattern and Dependency Injection</li>
                <li>Settup Logging using Serilog</li>
                <li>Understand the REST design principles</li>
                <li>Understand C# and .Net Core Web Syntax</li>
                <li>Understand user Authentication using JWT (JSON Web Tokens)</li>
                <li>Understand how to use Models, DTOs and Automapper</li>
                <li>Understand how to use NSwag to generate Http Client Code</li>
                <li>Manage Packages with NuGet Manager</li>
                <li>Setuo GitHub for Source Control</li>
                <li>Setup a Microsoft Azure Account</li>
                <li>Build Web Application to interact with Web API</li>
                <li>Deploy API and Database to Azure Web Database Services</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
